-- JPMorgan derivatives loss likely $4 billion to $6 billion
-- 
-- Thu Jun 28, 2012 2:46pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/06/28/us-jpmorgan-loss-size-idUSBRE85R1EU20120628

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - JPMorgan Chase & Co will likely lose $4 billion to $6 billion on its flawed derivatives portfolio, some two to three times as much as the company originally estimated, according to a person familiar with the matter. 
 JPMorgan declined to comment. (Reporting by David Henry in New York; Editing by Gerald E. McCormick.)